00:24:09.950 --> 00:24:15.680
Actually as I said, his mentor,
the man he loves so much,

00:24:15.680 --> 00:24:19.570
Socrates, hung out in the
Agora, in the marketplace

00:24:19.570 --> 00:24:24.540
of Athens, buttonholing
anybody he could

00:24:24.540 --> 00:24:28.200
and asking them his
very peculiar questions,

00:24:28.200 --> 00:24:33.170
and very high up people,
statesman, powerful people,

00:24:33.170 --> 00:24:40.645
rhetoricians, sophists, who were
itinerant professors sort of.

00:24:40.645 --> 00:24:44.770
But all the way down to
slaves-- it was a slave society.

00:24:44.770 --> 00:24:51.980
And Plato, after
Socrates' execution,

00:24:51.980 --> 00:24:55.210
after the Athenians
voted that he

00:24:55.210 --> 00:24:57.000
was guilty of the
two charges that

00:24:57.000 --> 00:24:59.850
were brought against him,
impiety and corrupting

00:24:59.850 --> 00:25:03.360
the young-- I have a theory
as to why they killed him

00:25:03.360 --> 00:25:09.590
when they did kill him--
that Plato left Athens.

00:25:09.590 --> 00:25:12.380
And he might have thought
his own life was in danger.

00:25:12.380 --> 00:25:17.170
But he was certainly
demoralized, disillusioned.

00:25:17.170 --> 00:25:18.910
And he left Athens.

00:25:18.910 --> 00:25:21.360
He traveled widely.

00:25:21.360 --> 00:25:23.150
Very importantly
for the development

00:25:23.150 --> 00:25:27.080
of his own point of view
as distinct from Socrates,

00:25:27.080 --> 00:25:31.520
he traveled to Italy, which was
the center of the Pythagorean

00:25:31.520 --> 00:25:32.150
community.

00:25:32.150 --> 00:25:35.320
So this view that
mathematics presents

00:25:35.320 --> 00:25:38.460
the key to
understanding the world.

00:25:38.460 --> 00:25:43.780
The intelligibility of the world
is given to us in mathematics.

00:25:43.780 --> 00:25:47.170
That had a very important
effect on Plato.

00:25:47.170 --> 00:25:53.830
But when he came back to Athens,
he didn't go to the Agora.

00:25:53.830 --> 00:25:59.480
That had proved to be pretty
fatal and futile he judged.

00:25:59.480 --> 00:26:01.670
And he found the Academy.

00:26:01.670 --> 00:26:06.570
He separated himself
from the mass of people.

00:26:06.570 --> 00:26:12.520
He had a very low opinion
of most people's potential

00:26:12.520 --> 00:26:15.050
for being rational, for
being able to think through.

00:26:15.050 --> 00:26:18.000
As you know, he developed the
idea of the philosopher king

00:26:18.000 --> 00:26:21.700
to make most of the decisions
for the masses of us.

00:26:21.700 --> 00:26:27.260
And he didn't give
one public lecture.

00:26:27.260 --> 00:26:32.480
And this is why I know he
